# Hamnix hpm LOCAL / on-image repo trust root — Ed25519 public key (32 bytes, hex).
#
# This is a SEPARATE trust root from etc/hpm/trusted.pub. It authenticates
# ONLY file:// (local / on-image installer) repositories, which are already
# trusted BY CONSTRUCTION (their bytes never cross a network and are covered
# by whatever authenticates the image as a whole). Because that boundary is
# not a network trust boundary, the matching SECRET (scripts/hpm_local_key.seed)
# is committed to the tree so every local / offline build can stamp its
# on-image index.json with a valid signature — this is an integrity stamp,
# NOT a defence against a network MITM. The REMOTE repo (255.one) is guarded
# by etc/hpm/trusted.pub, whose secret is held out of band and NEVER committed.
#
# The same 32 bytes are compiled into the hpm binary as the built-in local
# trust root; this file exists for inspection / tooling.
#
# Lines beginning with '#' are comments; the first bare token is the key.
ef17a867f9c2c000080674acbb66c0b849e21032e55188032f10e4625278cbe7
